Implementing state-of-the-art algorithms to enhance color, contrast and dynamic range, this is an easy-to-use image processing tool that will automatically improve digital images.

response.name: Image response
response.description: The response is a binary image with the same MIME Type as the input image.

data.name: Image Enhancement
colorCorrection
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) color correction. Default value is 0. Enabling it can be useful for photos with a dominant color (e.g. a photo where the snow looks blue)

data.name: contrastEnhance
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) contrast enhancement. Default value is 1.

data.name: contrastEnhanceBlack
data.description: Contrast enhancement intensity for the black component. It ranges from 0.0 to 20.0, default value is 4.0.

data.name: contrastEnhanceWhite
data.description: Contrast enhancement intensity for the white component. It ranges from 0.0 to 20.0, default value is 9.0.

data.name: file
data.description: Binary image file (please value one between url and file)

data.name: fillLight
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) fill light. Default value is 0. Enabling it will make dark photos look brighter.

data.name: fillLightIntensity
data.description: Fill light intensity ranges from 1.0 to 3.0. Default value is 1.0.

data.name: sharpen
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) sharpening. Default value is 0.

data.name: sharpenIntensity
data.description: Sharpness intensity ranges from 0.1 to 3.0. Default value is 0.3.

data.name: transferEnhanceIntensity
data.description: The main enhancement intensity parameter. It ranges from 0.1 to 1.0, default value is 0.3

data.name: transferEnhanceSensibility
data.description: The sensibility of the enhancement. The bigger the photo, the bigger it should be. It ranges from 1 to 9 (integer values), the default value is 1.

data.name: transferEnhanceSigma
data.description: This parameter represents the strength applied to the enhancement, it ranges from 0.1 to 4.0, the default value is 1.4.

data.name: url
data.description: URL of the image (please value one between url and file)
A filter that will make your real-world picture look like a miniature.

response.name: Image response
response.description: The response is a binary image with the same MIME Type as the input image.

data.name: Miniature Maker
colorSaturation
data.description: Painted or miniature models have generally more saturated colors than their real-world counterparts. The range of values for this parameter is from 0.0 to 1.0 ( default 0.8 ).

data.name: edgeSensibility
data.description: This parameter controls the edge preservation sensitivity. The higher the parameter value, the more edges will be preserved. The range of values for this parameter is from 0.1 to 5.0 ( default 2.0 ).

data.name: enhance
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) a simple image enhancement algorithm could be used after image simplification to make the resulting effect more evident.

data.name: file
data.description: Binary image file (please value one between url and file)

data.name: lensDistortion
data.description: Two kind of distortions are simulated:  Barrel (for parameter value > 0) : image magnification decreases with the distance from the focus point ( similar to a Fish Eye effect )  Pincushion (for parameter value < 0 ): image magnification increases with the distance from the focus point.  The higher (in absolute value) this parameter, the higher the lens distortion effect.  The range of values for this parameter is from -1.5 to 1.5 ( default 0.0 ).

data.name: shapeReduction
data.description: Painted or miniature models are generally poorer of details than their real counterparts. The simplify algoritmh iteratively flattens surfaces of represented objects while preserving their main adges thus reproducing the above mentioned effect. The range of values for this parameter is from 0 to 10 ( default 4 ).

data.name: simplify
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) the simplify algorithm. The goal of the simplify algoritmh is to simulate a painted or miniature -like model version from an existing real-world image. The simplify algorithm is enabled by default.

data.name: smoothIntensity
data.description: The higher, the stronger the smoothing effect into unfocused image areas. The range of values for this parameter is from 0.0 to 1.0 ( default 0.5 ).

data.name: tiltShift
data.description: Flag to enable (1) or disable (0) the tilt-shift effect. The well known miniature faking effect obtained optically using tilt-shift lenses produces selective-focused images. Disabled by default.

data.name: url
data.description: URL of the image (please value one between url and file)

data.name: x0
data.description: Top left corner x coordinate of the focus rectangle used by tilt shift. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0. Default value is 0.0.

data.name: x1
data.description: Bottom right corner x coordinate of the focus rectangle used by tilt shift. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0. Default value is 1.0.

data.name: y0
data.description: Top left corner y coordinate of the focus rectangle used by tilt shift. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0. Default value is 0.3.

data.name: y1
data.description: Bottom right corner y coordinate of the focus rectangle used by tilt shift. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0. Default value is 0.7.
It has never been so easy to remove red-eye from digital images. The focus of this function is to provide painless and error free results each and every time.

response.name: Image response
response.description: The response is a binary image with the same MIME Type as the input image.

data.name: Red Eye Correction
file
data.description: Binary image file (please value one between url and file)

data.name: intensity
data.description: Correction intensity to apply when correcting red eyes. It ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 4. The higher, the darker the corrected red eyes.

data.name: level
data.description: Tolerance level to apply when searching for red eyes. It ranges from 0 to 2 with a default value of 1. Using 0 the algorithm will less likely be tricked by false positives but will probably loose some hard-to-find red eyes. At 2 the algorithm will take some risks at identifying red eyes but will also find more of them.

data.name: url
data.description: URL of the image (please value one between url and file)
